The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                wenty passengers were injured when the bus they were travelling in fell into a roadside pond near Talsari in Howrah on Sunday. The injured have been admitted to Bagnan Gramin Hospital and Uluberia Sub-divisional Hospital. Police said the bus, carrying 40 passengers, overturned while trying to overtake another bus.   Thyroid cancer: Occurrence of thyroid cancer is on the rise in Bengal, said Anil DCruz, director, Tata Memorial Hospital, Mumbai. He was speaking at a seminar organised by the hospital and the Bengal Oncology Centre on Saturday.   Suicide: Srikanta Mondal, 35, a resident of Sonarpur, died after consuming poison on Saturday. He also fed the poison to son, Sekhar, 11, and daughter Puja, 10. While Puja died, Sekhar is in a critical state at National Medical College and Hospital. Police said Srikanta had a tiff with wife Sibani on Saturday over her alleged extra-marital affair.   Roadblock: Autorickshaw drivers backed by the Trinamul Congress blocked Ghoshpara Road in Barrackpore for two hours to protest the plying of illegal autos on the route.   Fire: A fire broke out at Prabartak Jute Mill in Agarpara on Sunday evening. Four tenders doused the flames in an hour.                                                                                                                                               
